Steps to install Git plugin
1. Install Git plugin in jenkins UI.
2. Install Git on the unix server.
3. Logon to jenkins server(UNIX server) and create a public key as jenkins user.
4. Copy the public key to github(in settings option)
5. In jenkins server, connect to git repo using below command(one time step)
	 ssh git@github01.lab.cloud-core.net
Note: Step 5 is to eliminate ssh message. If it is not run, jenkins job will get failed as it will be prompting ssh message.
END!!! 
